<br>
I’ve been debating over the past week if I should post this or not.  I think it is probably best to get the facts straight, as to curb any misleading information from being generated by the rumor factory.<br>
<br>
Let me start with a little dialog from my perspective as to what happened.  Basically, there were 3 wizards in PoF, one of them was there for his epic piece and I guess he wasn’t allowed in the drops.  This left myself (einweg) and Suenydar to lotto on armor drops.<br>
<br>
When some sleeves dropped, I had won two pieces, and I *thought* Suenydar won 1 piece.  So I sent him a tell asking if he had shoulders, he said he didn’t.  So I thought he should default on the arms.<br>
<br>
Our lotto master (Shabbate) called for tells on who is in the sleeves, I did not send a tell.  I then received a tell from her asking if I wanted the sleeves, I said yes, but that I had already won.  I thought that was clear enough.<br>
<br>
Shabbate called out the names to be lottoed, it was suenydar 1, einweg 2.  Now, I do not know why I was added to the lotto, but given that I had explained that I had already won previous loot, I figured our lotto master knew something I didn’t.  Perhaps suenydar had won more items, perhaps he didn’t want to default, or for another reason.  I don’t really know, but I was in the lotto even after I had explained that I had won.<br>
<br>
Shabbate rolled, and I won.  She said to loot, everyone else said to loot, so I looted.  After which I found out I was in the wrong.  With further investigation, it turns out this was a simple miscommunication among Shabbate, Suenydar and myself.<br>
<br>
Now, I realize this was wrong, so in an attempt to correct it, I petitioned.  After a few hours I was eventually able to speak with our (former) server GM, Vedan.  Basically, he said he wont transfer it.<br>
<br>
I can understand that Suenydar is upset, I have tried to make amends but he wont have it.  I have not, and have no intention to screw or cheat anyone.  I, along with several others believe this was an honest mistake.<br>
<br>
I have been on other raids with Suenydar, and he has always been a pleasant and competent person.  It is unfortunate that he and I can not come to terms about this issue.<br>
<br>
